components.title: Drivers of Spend and Trend By Setting (Current Period)

labels: Percent of Total PMPM Change (CP - PP)

footer.text: Utilization = Unique members divided by total unique members

components.description: Percent of Spend, Utilization (Percent of Members) and Percent of Total PMPM Change (CP – PP) by Setting for the Current Period only. These metrics are reported based on medical coverage. The Outpatient Setting is split by ER and Other Outpatient. Professional is split by PCP and various Specialist categories. The Percent of Spend is the cost or spend per setting divided by total cost or spend. The Utilization (Percent of Members) is the unique members per setting divided by total unique members. Percent of Total PMPM Change (CP – PP) is a trend or percent change of cost or paid per member per month (PMPM) from the Prior 1 Period to the Current Period.
